usic's expressive character, but need not depend on formal musicological training.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aArt History. 4aMusical Arts & Ethnomusicology. 4aPhilosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150173398740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501733987423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501733987/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles